.sh NAME
savw \*- read contents of GRINNELL window
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd savw
key [[-]mode]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Savw
transfers the contents of a GRINNELL memory window to the standard output.
Either image data or the overlay data may be read off in any raster scan
direction (left to right, right to left, bottom to top, etc.). Arguments
to the program select that portion of the data to be saved as well as
the direction of the scan. A 12-byte header containing number of columns,
number of rows, and bytes per pixel information will precede the data unless
the `-' is used with the
.it mode
argument.
.s3
.it Key
is one of:
.br
u6   upper 6 bits
.br
l6   lower 6 bits
.br
u8   upper 8 bits
.br
l8   lower 8 bits
.br
r    red
.br
g    green
.br
b    blue
.br
a    all twelve bits
.br
o    overlay only
.i0
.s3
.it Mode
specifies the direction of the scan:
.br
lb   left to right, bottom to top (default)
.br
lt   left to right, top to bottom (standard tv scan)
.br
rb   right to left, bottom to top
.br
rt   right to left, top to bottom
.br
bl   bottom to top, left to right
.br
br   bottom to top, right to left
.br
tl   top to bottom, left to right
.br
tr   top to bottom, right to left
.i0
